            <title>[MAHOUT-1189] CosineDistanceMeasure doesn&apos;t return 0 for two 0 vectors</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-1189</link>
                <project id="12310751" key="MAHOUT">Mahout</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;CosineDistanceMeasure for two equal vectors should always return 0 like for any other distance measure, however it returns 1.&lt;br/&gt;
This patch fixes this issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, note that it&apos;s not necessarily obvious what the return value should be since the cosine of two 0-length vectors isn&apos;t defined.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
